      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>This record refers to the work often transmitted under the title
               <foreign xml:lang="gez">Sayfa Śǝllāse</foreign> that consists of prayers for each day of the week. 
               It can be transmitted without miracles, but is often
                part of the collection <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2286ZenaSellase">Zenā nagaromu la-Śǝllāse</ref> in which the prayers for each
               day are followed
            each by a miracle of the Trinity. 
            This work is transmitted for example in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/SACEth002">Cairo, Société d’Archéologie Copte, Éthiopien 002</ref>,
               <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr53">Rome, Biblioteca dell’Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Conti Rossini 53</ref> or <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GAet10">Grottaferrata, Exarchic Greek Abbey of St. Mary of Grottaferrata, Crypt. Aet. 10</ref>.
            The identification of several recensions of this work or of works with a 
            similar structure but different textual content might be possible in the future.</p>
            <p>This work is different from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2281Trinity">Taʾammǝra Śǝllāse</ref> (a collection of miracles of the Trinity attributed
               to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2748BeduaA">Bǝḍuʿa ʾAmlāk</persName>) and from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2282Trinity">Taʾammǝra Śǝllāse</ref> (a collection of miracles of the 
               Trinity transmitted with <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1300Dersan">Dǝrsāna Śǝllāse</ref>).
               It is also different from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7331SaySelColl"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT7331SaySelColl</span></ref>, a collection also arranged according to the days of the week,
               whose prayers however correspond to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4691Prayer">Prayer for the weekdays</ref>.
            </p>
         </abstract>
